{
  "texts": [
    "Feature Engineering: 1.",
    "Feature selection and dimensionality reduction: Using principal component analysis (PCA) results, the first two principal components (PC1 and PC2) that explain the maximum variance are retained and treated as new features.",
    "Doing so helps reduce the dimensionality of the data set and preserves the most important information, simplifying the modeling process.2.",
    "Attach target column: Attach the target column (fraud) from the original data set to the new data set for use in classification tasks.",
    "In this way, the feature transformed by PCA can be associated with the target variable, and the relationship between the feature and the target can be better understood.3."
  ]
}